  "texts": [
    "The RAG-GPT model demonstrated a significantly higher accuracy after integrating the local knowledge base data than the GPT-4 group (8.6 ± 0.69 vs. 5.6 ± 0.96, p < 0.01).",
    "However, there was no statistically significant difference between the two groups for the secondary outcome measure of empathy (8.4 ± 0.85 vs. 7.8 ± 1.22, p > 0.05) (Table 2; Fig. 3).",
    "Breast cancer is one of the most common malignant tumors in women worldwide, and its treatment and care in clinical settings are challenging.",
    "In this study, we evaluated the application of RAG with LLM technology in breast cancer care for Q&A, compared with direct GPT-4.",
    "The results indicated that RAG technology can enhance the overall satisfaction with LLM responses to breast cancer care questions."
